BITTER RIDGE WIND FARM, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Bitter Ridge Wind Farm, LLC ("Bitter Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Bitter Ridge generating facility ("Bitter Ridge Facility").
The Bitter Ridge Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Jay County, Indiana. The Bitter Ridge Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Indiana Michigan Transmission Company, Inc. and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Bitter Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Bitter Ridge Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Bitter Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Bitter Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $597,296.52. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $49,774.71.
